headlines.description: — Rookie Brandon Miller made a career-high seven 3-pointers and finished with 31 points, and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 118-111 on Wednesday night to avenge a 23-point loss earlier in the week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Miller scores 31 points on career-high seven 3s as Hornets beat Cavaliers 118-111

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored 13 of his 23 points in the fourth quarter, Stephen Curry made the final two baskets of the game on an off shooting night and Golden State Warriors overcame Draymond Green's early ejection to beat the Orlando Magic 101-93 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors overcome Draymond Green’s early ejection to beat the Magic, 101-93

headlines.description: — Cam Thomas scored 38 points, including a pair of jumpers in overtime, and the Brooklyn Nets held off Washington 122-119 on Wednesday night, snapping the Wizards' modest three-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Thomas scores 38 points to help Nets snap Wizards' 3-game run with 122-119 overtime victory

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 30 points and seven assists and the Atlanta Hawks won their third in a row and handed Portland its eighth straight loss, beating the Trail Blazers 120-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dejounte Murray scores 30 points, Hawks hand Trail Blazers 8th straight loss with 120-106 victory

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard completed two 3-point plays late in the game then made a block at the rim on the final possession to lead the Los Angeles Clippers to a controversial 108-107 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kawhi Leonard comes alive late to lead Clippers to disputed 108-107 win over 76ers

events.name: New York Knicks at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Miles McBride matched a career-high with 29 points, Jalen Brunson had 26 and New York never trailed in a 145-101 win over the slumping Toronto Raptors on Wednesday night, the Knicks' biggest margin of victory this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: McBride scores 29, Robinson returns from injury and Knicks rout reeling Raptors 145-101

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 27 points and Nikola Vucevic added 22 with 12 rebounds to lead the Chicago Bulls past the Indiana Pacers 125-99 on Wednesday night to snap a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, Vucevic lead Bulls past Pacers 125-99 to end 3-game losing streak

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — LeBron James had a triple-double with 23 points, 14 rebounds and 12 assists, Rui Hachimura scored 32 points as the Los Angeles Lakers built a big lead in the third quarter and beat the Memphis Grizzlies 136-124 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James has triple-double to help Lakers beat Grizzlies, 136-124

headlines.description: — Naz Reid had 21 points and 10 rebounds and Jaden McDaniels added 20 points to help the Minnesota Timberwolves overcome a sluggish start Wednesday night to beat the <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Pistons 106-91 to hit 50-win mark for 5th time in franchise's 35 seasons

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Houston Rockets didn’t care that they beat an Oklahoma City squad that was missing its best player, All-Star guard Shai Gilgeous-Alexander.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 37, Rockets beat Thunder 132-126 in overtime for 10th straight victory

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Devin Vassell scored 31 points, Victor Wembanyama had 19 points and five blocks and the San Antonio Spurs ran past the Utah Jazz 118-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vassell scores 31 and Wembanyama has 19 points and 5 blocks to lead Spurs past Jazz 118-111

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 30 points, 13 rebounds and five blocks and the Phoenix Suns won in Denver for the second time this month, beating the defending champion Nuggets 104-97 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 30 points to lead Suns to another win in Denver, 104-97
